
1. Task List: Display a list of tasks, including their text, completion status, and priority level.
2. Add Task: Allow users to add new tasks to the list.
3. Task Completion: Enable users to mark tasks as completed or toggle their completion status.
4. Task Removal: Provide the ability to remove tasks from the list.
5. Task Editing: Allow users to edit the text of existing tasks. This feature also gives users the ability to organize their tasks according to priority. 


With this MVP, users can create a list of tasks, mark them as complete, remove tasks they no longer need, and edit the text of existing tasks. It covers the essential features needed for users to manage their tasks effectively.

As you progress, you can enhance the application by adding additional features such as adding due dates, or incorporating user authentication.